<td class="tabs"><a href="#social-democracy" class="tab" title="The Second International, founded in the 1880s and later the Labour Parties of the world">Social&#160;Democracy</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#reformism" class="tab" title="Social Democrats who wanted to achieve socialism by gradual reform, not revolution: 1880s - 1914">Reformists</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#fabianism" class="tab" title="A British group of socialists who advocated reforms to avoid revolution: 1890s/1900s">Fabians</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#bolsheviks" class="tab" title="Lenin and The Russian Social Democrats who made the October 1917 Revolution">The&#160;Bolsheviks</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#early-comintern" class="tab" title="Communists across the world who rallied behind the Bolsheviks from 1919">Early&#160;Comintern</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#comintern" class="tab" title="The Communist Parties of the world, from the mid-1920s - 1980s">Comintern</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#soviet-writers" class="tab" title="Soviet writers who applied Marxist ideas to different branches of science: 1914-1961">Soviet&#160;Science</a></td>
</tr><tr style="background: #000055;">
<td class="tabs"><a href="#soviet-marxism" class="tab" title="Writers who continued Marxism in the guise of science and philosophy: 1924-1979">Soviet&#160;Marxism</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#western-marxism" class="tab" title="After capitalism stablised, Marxists faced new strategic problems, from the mid-1920s - 1990s">Western&#160;Marxism</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#french-left" class="tab" title="The French intellectuals and students who offered new directions: 1953-1974">French&#160;Left</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#frankfurt-school" class="tab" title="A 'Communist University' founded in 1923 and still operative today: 1923-1998">Frankfurt&#160;School</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#trotskyism" class="tab" title="Founded by Bolsheviks and other Communists who supported the Russian  Revolution but opposed Stalin: 1923-2004">Trotskyists</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#left-communism" class="tab" title="Communists who opposed governmental power as a strategy for socialism: 1902-1978, and recent Left communists in Asia, 1978-1994">Left&#160;Communism</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#marxist-humanism" class="tab" title="Socialists who opposed ideas of structuralism and historical determinism, 1950s/60s">Marxist&#160;Humanism</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#market-socialism" class="tab" title="Communists who advocated the opening up of the market within socialist society: 1972-1989">Market&#160;Socialists</a></td>
</tr><tr style="background: #335533;">
<td class="tabs"><a href="#guerilla-marxism" class="tab" title="Marxists who advocated guerilla warfare in the countryside: 1959-1969">Guerilla Marxism</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#maoism" class="tab" title="Followers of Mao Zedong 1917-1975, and India's Naxalbari">Maoists</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#national-liberation" class="tab" title="Leaders of the national liberation movement against colonialism: 1950s/60s">National&#160;Liberation</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#african-liberation" class="tab" title="Pan-Africanism and the South African Communist Partyk, 1961-1998">African&#160;Liberation</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#black-liberation" class="tab" title="The Black Panthers 1966-998, and their predecessors, 1800-1859">Black&#160;Liberation</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#french-revolution" class="tab" title="Writers of the Great French Revolution of 1789-1799">French&#160;Revolution</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#paris-commune" class="tab" title="The Parisian workers who took power in 1871">Paris&#160;Commune</a></td>
<td class="tabs"><a href="#utopianism" class="tab" title="Pioneers of socialism who imagined a better world: 1515-1888">Utopianism</a></td>
