(1883&ndash;1938)	&lt; 5<br />            
Bolshevik leader, Secretary of the Military Revolutionary Committee of the Petrograd Soviet, led the attack on the Winter Palace, leading figure in Red Army during the Civil War (particularly in Ukraine), critic of NEP, Soviet diplomat &ndash; Soviet Consul General in Barcel during repression of POUM, recalled to Moscow (August 1937), arrested (October 1937) and shot (February 1938).            
