<br /><hr /><br /> <br />            
<img src="images/ci.jpg" alt="Communist International" hspace="10" vspace="2" border="0" align="left" height="100" />            
<h4><a href="../history/international/comintern/index.htm" name="early-comintern">The Comintern</a></h4>            
In 1919, the Bolsheviks held a conference attended by revolutionaries from every corner of the world, and established the Communist International (Comintern); soon there were Communist Parties in every country, drawing the most militant workers to the Bolsheviks. 
	After its dissolution in 1943,&nbsp; the various parties that had made it up 
	kept in touch through the Information Bureau of the Communist and Workers&#39; 
	Parties (Cominform), and through various international conferences.<p> <br />            
	</p>
<hr />            
</td></tr>            
            
            
