<td class="note" valign="top" width="50%">            
<img src="../glossary/people/s/pics/stalin.jpg" alt="Stalin" hspace="30" vspace="1" border="1" align="right" height="120" />            
<p class="fst">&#8220;<a href="../reference/archive/stalin/works/1924/12.htm" class="cite">The final victory of socialism in the first country to emancipate itself is impossible without the combined efforts of the proletarians of several countries, and the unfolding of the world revolution will be the more rapid and thorough, the more effective the assistance rendered by the first socialist country to the workers and laboring masses of all other countries.</a>&#8221;<br /></p>             
<span class="subject"><a href="../history/international/comintern/sections/britain/profiles.htm" class="group">British Communist Party</a></span><br />            
The CPGB History Archive includes a number of writers who were members of the Communist Party of Great Britain, including <a href="../archive/arnot-page/index.htm" class="member">R. Page Arnot</a>, <a href="../archive/bell/index.htm" class="member">Thomas Bell</a>, <a href="../archive/bradley/index.htm" class="member">B. F. Bradley</a>, <a href="../archive/brown-tom/index.htm" class="member">Tom Brown</a>, <a href="../archive/burns-emile/index.htm" class="member">Emile Burns</a>, <a href="../archive/campbell-jr/index.htm" class="member">J. R. Campbell</a>, <a href="../archive/cornforth/index.htm" class="member">Maurice Conforth</a>, <a href="../archive/cox/index.htm" class="member">Idris Cox</a>, <a href="../archive/crawfurd/index.htm" class="member">Helen Crawfurd</a>, <a href="../archive/dobb/index.htm" class="member">Maurice Dobb</a>, <a href="../archive/dutt-clemens/index.htm" class="member">Clemens Dutt</a>, <a href="../archive/fineberg/index.htm" class="member">Joseph Fineberg</a>, <a href="../archive/fox/index.htm" class="member">Ralph Fox</a>, <a href="../archive/gallacher/index.htm" class="member">Will Gallacher</a>, <a href="../archive/gollan/index.htm" class="member">John Gollan</a>, <a href="../archive/hannington/index.htm" class="member">Wal Hannington</a>, <a href="../archive/horner/index.htm" class="member">Arthur Horner</a>, <a href="../archive/horrabin/index.htm" class="member">J. F. Horrabin</a>, <a href="../archive/inkpin/index.htm" class="member">Albert Inkpin</a>, <a href="../archive/jackson-ta/index.htm" class="member">T. A. Jackson</a>, <a href="../archive/johnstone/index.htm" class="member">Monty Johnstone</a>, <a href="../archive/klugmann/index.htm" class="member">James Klugmann</a>, <a href="../archive/mcmanus/index.htm" class="member">Arthur MacManus</a>, <a href="../archive/morton/index.htm" class="member">A. L. Morton</a>, <a href="../archive/newbold/index.htm" class="member">J. T. Walton Newbold</a>, <a href="../archive/paul/index.htm" class="member">Eden &amp; Cedar Paul</a>, <a href="../archive/paul-william/index.htm" class="member">William Paul</a>, <a href="../archive/pollitt-marjorie/index.htm" class="member">Marjorie Pollitt</a>, <a href="../archive/postgate/index.htm" class="member">R. W. Postgate</a>, <a href="../archive/purkis/index.htm" class="member">Stewart Purkis</a>, <a href="../archive/quelch-tom/index.htm" class="member">Tom Quelch</a>, <a href="../archive/ramelson/index.htm" class="member">Bert Ramelson</a>, <a href="../archive/rothstein-andrew/index.htm" class="member">Andrew Rothstein</a>, <a href="../archive/rothstein/index.htm" class="member">Theodor Rothstein</a>, <a href="../archive/rust/index.htm" class="member">William Rust</a>, <a href="../archive/saklatvala/index.htm" class="member">Shapurji Saklatvala</a>, <a href="../archive/strachey/index.htm" class="member">John Strachey</a>, <a href="../archive/turner-beth/index.htm" class="member">Beth Turner</a>, <a href="../archive/wilkinson/index.htm" class="member">Ellen Wilkinson</a>, <a href="../archive/winternitz/index.htm" class="member">Joseph Winternitz</a>, <a href="../archive/wintringham/index.htm" class="member">Tom Wintringham</a>, <a href="../archive/woddis/index.htm" class="member">Jack Woddis</a>,  and others as well as fellow-travellers such as <a href="../archive/johnson-hewlett/index.htm" class="member">Hewlett Johnson</a>.             
