<h4><a href="../history/etol/writers/ist/index.htm" class="group" name="international-socialists">International Socialist Tendency</a></h4>            
<p class="fst"><br />            
<img src="../glossary/people/c/pics/cliff.jpg" alt="Tony Cliff" hspace="10" vspace="2" border="1" align="right" height="100" />            
&#8220;<a href="cliff/works/1948/stalruss/intro.htm" class="cite">Just as it became necessary to discard the slogan of the &#8216;democratic dictatorship of the proletariat and peasantry&#8217; after the Bolshevik Party had existed for 14 years, so has it now become necessary to renounce the theory of Russia as a degenerated workers&#8217; state</a>.&#8221;</p>            
<span class="author"><a href="cliff/index.htm" class="red">Tony Cliff</a></span>            
(1917&ndash;2000)	50+ <img class="auto" src="images/red-star.jpg" alt="*" width="11" height="10" /><br />            
Palestinian Jewish Trotskyist, developed critique of Stalinist Russia as a form of &ldquo;bureaucratic state capitalism&rdquo;, laid the basis of the theory of 'deflected' permanent revolution and the &lsquo;permanent&rsquo; arms economy, founder of International Socialist Tendency.            
<br />            
[<a class="biog" href="../glossary/people/c/l.htm#cliff-tony">Biography</a>]            
<br />            
<br />            
<span class="author"><a href="hallas/index.htm" class="red">Duncan Hallas</a></span>            
(1925&ndash;2002) 40+<br />            
British Trotskyist, leading member of the International Socialists and later of the British Socialist Workers Party.<br />            
[<a class="biog" href="../glossary/people/h/a.htm#hallas-duncan">Biography</a>]            
<br />            
<br />            
<span class="author"><a href="../history/etol/writers/manning/index.htm" class="red">Brian Manning</a></span>            
(1927&ndash;2004) 5+<br />            
British Marxist historian of the English Revolution, student of Christopher Hill, associated with the New Left in the 1950s and early 1960s, later joined Irish SWP.<br />           
<br />            
<br />            
<span class="author"><a href="../history/etol/writers/challinor/index.htm" class="red">Raymond Challinor</a></span>            
(1929&ndash;2011) 60+<br />            
British Trotskyist, Marxist historian and a founder member of the Socialist Review Group, and later member of International Socialists.           
<br />
<br />         
<span class="author"><a href="kidron/index.htm" class="small-red">Michael Kidron</a></span>            
(1930&ndash;2003) 10+	<br />            
A leading theoretician of the British Socialist Review Group and its successor, the International Socialists; also an editor of several publications including Pluto Press.
<br />            
<br />	            
<span class="author"><a href="higgins/index.htm" class="small-red">Jim Higgins</a></span>            
(1930&ndash;2002) 10+	<br />            
British postal worker and trade unionist, prominent member of International Socialists in late 1960s and early 1970s, a founder of the ISO.<br />            
[<a class="biog" href="../glossary/people/h/i.htm#higgins-jim">Biography</a>]            
