<p class="fst"><img src="../glossary/people/h/pics/hegel.gif" alt="Hegel" hspace="30" vspace="1" border="1" align="right" height="120" /> &#8220;<a href="../reference/subject/philosophy/works/ge/hegel2.htm" class="cite">The history of philosophy deals not with a past, but with an eternal and veritable present: and resembles not a museum of the aberrations of the human intellect, but a Pantheon of godlike figures, one after another in dialectical development.</a>&#8221;</p>            
